   "source": [
    "# Manager Effectiveness Analysis\n",
    "### Based on Google Project Oxygen\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Tobi Abanishe  \n",
    "**Portfolio:** [github.com/TobiAbanishe](https://github.com/TobiAbanishe)  \n",
    "**Project:** HR Analytics Portfolio — Project 2  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "In 2008, Google launched **Project Oxygen** to answer a simple question: do managers actually matter, and if so, what makes a good one? After analysing performance reviews, surveys, and interviews across thousands of teams, they found that manager quality is one of the strongest predictors of team performance, retention, and employee satisfaction.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project operationalises the Project Oxygen framework using a simulated dataset of 60 managers across six departments. The analysis covers four areas:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Survey Response Analysis** — how employees rated their managers on the 8 Oxygen behaviors  \n",
    "2. **Manager Effectiveness Score** — a composite score built from all behavior ratings  \n",
    "3. **Team Outcome Correlations** — how effectiveness scores relate to attrition, engagement, and performance  \n",
    "4. **Manager Clustering** — grouping managers into effectiveness tiers for targeted interventions  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## The 8 Google Project Oxygen Behaviors\n",
    "\n",
    "| # | Behavior |\n",
    "|---|----------|\n",
    "| 1 | Is a good coach |\n",
    "| 2 | Empowers the team and does not micromanage |\n",
    "| 3 | Creates an inclusive environment, shows concern for success and wellbeing |\n",
    "| 4 | Is productive and results-oriented |\n",
    "| 5 | Is a good communicator — listens and shares information |\n",
    "| 6 | Supports career development and discusses performance |\n",
    "| 7 | Has a clear vision and strategy for the team |\n",
    "| 8 | Has key technical skills to help advise the team |\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
