    "---\n",
    "## 3. Manager Effectiveness Score\n",
    "\n",
    "The **Manager Effectiveness Score** is a composite metric built from a manager's average rating across all 8 Oxygen behaviors. The steps are:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. For each manager, compute the mean rating per behavior across all survey respondents.\n",
    "2. Average the 8 behavior means into one raw score (scale: 1 to 5).\n",
    "3. Normalise to a 0 to 100 scale for easier communication with stakeholders: `score = (raw - 1) / 4 * 100`\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Step 1: Average behavior ratings per manager\n",
    "mgr_behavior_avg = survey.groupby('manager_id')[BEHAVIOR_COLS].mean().reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 2: Composite raw score (1-5)\n",
    "mgr_behavior_avg['raw_score'] = mgr_behavior_avg[BEHAVIOR_COLS].mean(axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Step 3: Normalise to 0-100\n",
    "mgr_behavior_avg['effectiveness_score'] = (mgr_behavior_avg['raw_score'] - 1) / 4 * 100\n",
    "\n",
    "# Merge with manager info\n",
    "mgr_scores = mgr_behavior_avg.merge(managers, on='manager_id')\n",
    "\n",
    "print('Effectiveness score summary:')\n",
    "print(mgr_scores['effectiveness_score'].describe().round(2))\n"
   ]
  },
